    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Out of habit, we ask when someone dies,&lt;br&gt;
&amp;ldquo;Oh, how did he die?&amp;rdquo;&lt;br&gt;
He was young,&lt;br&gt;
He was good, religious,&lt;br&gt;
He practiced yoga, cared for his health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Out of habit, we ask when someone suffers,&lt;br&gt;
&amp;ldquo;Oh, why is he suffering?&amp;rdquo;&lt;br&gt;
He is a good person,&lt;br&gt;
A virtuous soul.&lt;br&gt;
Sometimes we say,&lt;br&gt;
&amp;ldquo;He has already suffered enough,&lt;br&gt;
Why must he endure more?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
